What would be the function&#39;s signature?
&lt;pre&gt;
val nth : int -&gt; &#39;a * &#39;b * &#39;c -&gt; ???
&lt;/pre&gt;

Depending on the goals, we can get away with this by writing multiple functions, or wrapping the result in a special container of a new type. The first approach gives us this:
&lt;pre&gt;
val first : &#39;a * &#39;b * &#39;c -&gt; &#39;a
val second : &#39;a * &#39;b * &#39;c -&gt; &#39;b
val third : &#39;a * &#39;b * &#39;c -&gt; &#39;c
&lt;/pre&gt;

The second approach involves wrapping the result in a variant:
&lt;pre&gt;
type (&#39;a, &#39;b, &#39;c) proj = First of &#39;a | Second of &#39;b | Third of &#39;c
val nth : int -&gt; &#39;a * &#39;b * &#39;c -&gt; (&#39;a, &#39;b, &#39;c) proj
&lt;/pre&gt;

