I am supposing that `lstproductdetail` is the name of the array that all the products and `lstproduct` is how you show one product&#39;s data. 

In such case, the quantity of your product should not be shown as a common property `Itemquantity`. The quantity should differ and should be unique for each product. For eg, `lstproduct.quantity` (the same way you are showing different price for each different product).

Similarly then, when you&#39;ll increment the quantity you can pass a unique id of the object lstproduct in the function and can increment this particular object&#39;s quantity. I am going to show you how to do this with index.


Eg,

In HTML:

Change - `&lt;ion-item *ngFor=&quot;let lstproduct of lstproductdetail; let i=index&quot;&gt;`

In TS:

    eaddItem(value: any, i) { 
         const initialvalue = 0; 
         if (value != null) { 
             const afterclick = value + 1; 
             return (this.lstproductdetail[i].Itemquantity = afterclick); 
         } 
         else { 
             return (this.lstproductdetail[i].Itemquantity = initialvalue + 1); 
         } 
    } 
    
    decrementItem(value: any, i) { 
        const initialvalue = 1; 
        if (value &gt; 0) { 
            const afterclick = value - 1; 
            return (this.lstproductdetail[i].Itemquantity = afterclick); 
        } 
        else { 
            return (this.lstproductdetail[i].Itemquantity = initialvalue - 1); 
        } 
    } 

This way, the quantity will change for only the product this function is called on.

